<TITLE> Pakistan set to gamble with seamer Riaz </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, June 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistan look set to gamble with inexperienced left arm seamer Wahab Riaz when they play Sri Lanka in a crucial match in the super league of the Asia Cup one-day tournament on Sunday. Australian coach Geoff Lawson told reporters after a net session that Riaz, who celebrated his 23rd birthday on Saturday, is in line to replace the injured Umar Gul. "Riaz is likely to play because we know it is a tough game against Sri Lanka who have the advantage of having carried forward two points from the qualifying stage," Lawson said. Riaz has played only four one-dayers and in his last appearance against India in the tri-series in Dhaka earlier this month he was savaged for 86 runs
